description:
Department of Chemistry, Sri Venkateswara University,&nbsp;Tirupati-517 502 

  Manuscript received 3 September 1981, revised  5  July 1982,accepted 27 October 1983  

 THERE is a paucity of literature on the amperometric determination of manganese(II), particularly using oximes as titrants. During a detailed investigation on the utility of 2.-hydroxy-1-acetonaphthoneoxime (2-HANO) and its Isomer, l-hydroxy-2-acetonaphthoneoxime(l-HAN0) 1  as analytical reagents, it was observed that both the reagents give dark green precipitates with Mn(II) at pH 8.0-8.5. These reactions were utilised for the amperemetric determination of Mn(II) in view of the favourable polarographic behaviour of Mn(II). The results of investigations on the use of 2-HANO as an amperometric titrant for Mn(II) are presented here. The reagent has already been used for gravimetric 2,3 &nbsp;and amperometric 4 &nbsp;determination of copper, nickel&nbsp;and palladium. 

